events.description: Weekly social casual chess for women, non-binary players, and girls. All skill levels welcome! Coaching sessions, friendly games, and socializing. Building a safe and engaging space for women in chess.

events.description: DC's premiere social chess club! Meet new friends over casual games. All levels from beginner to expert. Chess sets provided. 21+ venue with great atmosphere.

events.description: Chess and games café in heart of Amsterdam's Jordaan district. Different beers on tap, nice staff, good atmosphere. Great for casual chess and meeting locals!

events.description: Chic chess bar in Saint-Germain-des-Prés with 27 tables. Jazz music atmosphere. Afterwork events, team building. Wine selection and gourmet food. All levels welcome!

events.description: Weather permitting outdoor chess! Bring your own board or find pickup games. Classic NYC chess culture. Great for beginners to watch and learn from street chess masters.

events.description: Many libraries host weekly chess clubs! Call your local library. Usually free, family-friendly, and perfect for beginners. Equipment provided. Great way to learn in supportive environment.
